  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "A good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon depends a little on what role you want it to fill early on and what you want its evolved form, Lycanroc, to do later. Here's a general, versatile moveset for Rockruff that will work well during the main story, along with considerations for evolving into Midday, Midnight, or Dusk Form Lycanroc:\n\n**General Rockruff Moveset (Early Game)**\n\n*   **Bite (Dark-type):** Level Up (Lv. 12). Great coverage early on, hits Ghost and Psychic types that Rock-types struggle against.  A solid STAB option until you get a better Rock move.\n\n*   **Rock Throw (Rock-type):** Level Up (Lv. 15). Your first reliable STAB Rock-type move.\n\n*   **Leer (Normal-type):** Level Up (Starting move) A useful move for reducing the opponent's defense. This can help you do more damage.\n\n*   **Rock Tomb (Rock-type):** TM22. Slows down the opponent. Makes Rockruff faster in comparison, thus helping it outspeed its targets.\n\n**Explanation & Considerations:**\n\n*   **Early Game Priority:** Rockruff is pretty straightforward early on. You want to exploit type matchups. Bite helps against common early-game threats like Ghost-types.\n*   **TMs:** Sun and Moon have reusable TMs, so don't be afraid to use them.\n*   **Evolution:** Plan ahead for the Lycanroc form you want.  Lycanroc forms have different stats and movepools.\n\n**Evolution Considerations for Lycanroc:**\n\n**Lycanroc (Midday Form):**\n\n*   **Focus:**  Speed and Physical Attack.  This form is a fast attacker.\n*   **Key Stats:** High Speed and Attack.\n*   **Typical Moves:**  Accelerock, Stone Edge, Close Combat, Sucker Punch\n\n**Lycanroc (Midnight Form):**\n\n*   **Focus:** Power and bulk.  This form is more of a physical wallbreaker/attacker.\n*   **Key Stats:** High Attack, decent HP and Defense.\n*   **Typical Moves:**  Counter, Stone Edge, Accelerock, Psychic Fangs.\n\n**Lycanroc (Dusk Form):**\n\n*   **Focus:** A mix of both Midday and Midnight. More rounded stats.\n*   **Key Stats:** Balanced Attack, Speed, and Defenses.\n*   **Typical Moves:** Accelerock, Stone Edge, Swords Dance, Outrage (Egg Move).\n\n**Adapting the Moveset After Evolution:**\n\nOnce Rockruff evolves, you'll want to tailor its moveset to the strengths of its form:\n\n*   **Replace Bite:**  Lycanroc learns much better moves as it levels up, so get rid of Bite.\n\n*   **Add Stronger STAB:** Replace Rock Throw with a more powerful Rock-type move as soon as possible. **Stone Edge (TM71)** is the ultimate choice for raw power. However, Stone Edge's accuracy is not the best. \n    *   For more reliable accuracy but less power, **Rock Slide (TM76)** is a good choice for double battles, and **Accelerock** (Learned at level 45 (Midday and Dusk Form) & Level 40 (Midnight Form)) gives you priority.\n\n*   **Coverage Moves:** Lycanroc can learn a few good coverage moves. **Close Combat (TM42)** is excellent for Fighting-type coverage. **Psychic Fangs (Level 50 Midnight form)** can destroy screens and hit for super effective damage against Psychic and Ghost types.\n\n**Key Move Considerations for Lycanroc Forms:**\n\n*   **Midday:**  Accelerock is key for this form.\n*   **Midnight:** Counter can punish physical attackers.\n*   **Dusk:** Accelerock is again very useful here. Outrage is a powerful coverage move (but has drawbacks).\n\n**Remember to adjust your moveset based on what you're facing!** This is a flexible foundation to start with. Experiment and find what works best for your play style! Good luck!\n",
